ual gorillas like Beethoven, Digit, Uncle Bert and Old Goat. Which makes the overall feel of the work all the more tragic. I don't think it's spoiling anything to say that in the struggle for survival between endangered species and human negligence, obstinance and cruelty, humans all too often come out on top. That's usually the case in \u003ci\u003eGorillas in the Mist\u003c/i\u003e as well, and Fossey does not spare us the details – nor should she. Eventually, it seems likely work like hers will be the only way to bring back these creatures after they recede into the mists forever.","rating":4,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/16092014?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"science","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/16092014?shelf=science"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2521446891"},"likeCount":7,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":1,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:10770371":{"id":10770371,"__typename":"User","legacyId":10770371,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1540580928i/10770371._UX200_CR0,50,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":874,"viewableName":"Dan","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/10770371-dan","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":53},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.gbpRStiXBoSRJJDoC8Lbxw":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.gbpRStiXBoSRJJDoC8Lbxw","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.6CPNjLTSGAinB3tto9VFqQ"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:10770371"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1628888387323,"createdAt":1628445446978,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1628619686300,"text":"Dian Fossey's groundbreaking research on the mountain gorillas of Uganda and Rwanda began in 1967 and continued until her death in 1985. This book was published just two years before she was murdered by poachers at her research station in Volcanoes Parc in Rwanda. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThis book is well written but it uses a diary like format that at times plods along and at times is too cathartic for my maximum enjoyment. Since there are so many gorillas to keep track of in the book there are only a few of these relationships that I could take to heart.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eIn comparison to another primate specialist, I would say that Jane Goodall is a better writer. But Fossey's story is pretty remarkable. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eIt should be noted that when this book was written there were only 200 mountain gorillas in the wild. Largely because of Fossey's conservation efforts in Rwanda over eighteen years (1967-1985) there are nearly 2,000 mountain gorillas that live in the wild today. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eWhat makes the book so special? Dian Fossey's almost single minded devotion to her research and the calculated risks that she took. The world needs more Dian Fosseys! \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e4 stars.","rating":4,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/10770371?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"environment","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/10770371?shelf=environment"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2698585769"},"likeCount":6,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":0,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:17388876":{"id":17388876,"__typename":"User","legacyId":17388876,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1539160298i/17388876._UX200_CR0,33,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":91,"viewableName":"Grace","isBlockedByViewer":f